model.ruby_template:
#!/bin/ruby

def countSolutions(a, b, c, d)
    # Complete this function
end

q = gets.strip.to_i
for a0 in (0..q-1)
    a, b, c, d = gets.strip.split(' ')
    a = a.to_i
    b = b.to_i
    c = c.to_i
    d = d.to_i
    result = countSolutions(a, b, c, d)
    puts result;

model.haskell_template:
import Control.Applicative
import Control.Monad
import System.IO


main :: IO ()
main = do
    q_temp <- getLine
    let q = read q_temp :: Int
    forM_ [1..q] $ \a0  -> do
        a_temp <- getLine
        let a_t = words a_temp
        let a = read $ a_t!!0 :: Int
        let b = read $ a_t!!1 :: Int
        let c = read $ a_t!!2 :: Int
        let d = read $ a_t!!3 :: Int


getMultipleLines :: Int -> IO [String]

getMultipleLines n
    | n <= 0 = return []
    | otherwise = do          
        x <- getLine         
        xs <- getMultipleLines (n-1)    
        let ret = (x:xs)    
        return ret

-module(solution).
-export([main/0]).

main() ->

    { ok, [Q]} = io:fread("", "~d"),
    Q_list = lists:seq(1,Q),
    lists:foreach( fun(Q0) ->
            { ok, [A,B,C,D]} = io:fread("", "~d~d~d~d")
    end,Q_list),
    true.

read_array(0,D) -> [];
read_array(N,D) -> 
	{ok, [X]} = io:fread("", D),
	[X | read_array(N-1,D)].

read_2darray(0,M,D) -> [];
read_2darray(N,M,D) ->
	Q=read_array(M,D),
	[Q | read_2darray(N-1,M,D)].
